C=====False=====54
This empire was governed by the Gbara, which drew delegates from its territories across the “Twelve
Doors” and was formed by the Kouroukan Fouga constitution. According to myth, a rooster-tipped arrow
allowed this empire to win the Battle of Kirina. A ruler of this empire allegedly devalued gold throughout
North Africa with his lavish gifts while on a hajj to Mecca. For the point, name this West African empire
that was supplanted by the Songhai and was once ruled by Mansa Musa.=====
Mali Empire
